text: Pobeda () is a rural locality (a village) in Sikiyazsky Selsoviet, Duvansky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 20 as of 2010. There is 1 street. == Geography == It is located 5 km from Mesyagutovo, 5 km from Sikiyaz. == References == Category:Rural localities in Duvansky District
title: Pobeda, Duvansky District, Republic of Bashkortostan
